  "market_context": "Tesla daily chart showing a strong prior uptrend with multiple higher lows and higher highs, followed by a pullback testing the lower boundary of an uptrend channel; horizontal resistance at ~378.17 previously held multiple times before breakout.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst observed that Tesla was testing the bottom of an upward-sloping trend channel and highlighted how horizontal resistance at 378.17 had previously caused price rejection before a major upside breakout.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst selected the Trend Line tool and drew an upward-sloping line connecting consecutive higher lows to define the uptrend.",
    "Step 2: Using Ctrl+C/Ctrl+V, the analyst duplicated the trend line to create a parallel upper line, forming a trend channel enclosing the majority of candles from late October to mid-January.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted Tesla was currently testing the lower boundary of the trend channel, warning that a strong break below could signal trend reversal or sideways transition.",
    "Step 4: The analyst demonstrated drawing an ascending triangle pattern by connecting higher lows with an upward-sloping trend line and a horizontal resistance line at the top of the consolidation.",
    "Step 5: The analyst switched to the Horizontal Line tool and drew a resistance level at 378.17, identifying it as a key zone where price reacted multiple times before breaking out upward.",
    "Step 6: The analyst pointed out that the breakout above the 378.17 resistance marked the start of a massive upside move."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Trend lines and horizontal levels are essential for visualizing market structure; uptrend channels help identify potential support zones, while repeated rejections at horizontal resistance confirm its significance before breakout.",
